Revision history for Virani

?.?.?  ?/?
       - Virani::Client now percent encodes every value it places in the query
         string when contacting mojo-virani, so a filter, set, type, or cache
         ID containing reserved characters (& # = + %, spaces, IPv6 ':') can no
         longer corrupt the request or inject query parameters... previously
         only spaces in the filter were encoded... this is wire compatible with
         existing mojo-virani servers, which decode the values via $c->param
       - add a PCAP hosts cache... Virani->update_pcap_hosts indexes what
         hosts are in each PCAP of a set via tshark with
         '-n -q -z endpoints,ipv4 -z endpoints,ipv6', saving them as newline
         delimited lists under $cache/pcap_hosts/$set/ named after the PCAP's
         path relative to the set path, with entries invalidated via mtime
         comparison against the PCAP, PCAPs modified less than
         pcap_hosts_min_age seconds ago (default 120, settable globally or
         per set) skipped to avoid indexing PCAPs still being written to,
         and entries for removed PCAPs pruned... readable per PCAP via
         Virani->read_pcap_hosts and updatable via virani
         --update-pcap-hosts, intended for cron
       - add Virani->get_sets for getting a list of configured sets, exposed
         via mojo-virani as the get_sets=1 param and remotely fetchable via
         Virani::Client->get_sets or virani --list-sets
       - get_pcap_local can now use the PCAP hosts index to skip PCAPs that
         can not match a host filter before the per PCAP filtering... when the
         new host_pruning config var is enabled (globally or per set, default
         off) and the filter requires one or more IP hosts, the filter is
         reduced to OR-of-AND-groups of hosts and a time matched PCAP is kept
         only when its indexed host list fully contains at least one group, so
         'host A and host B' drops a PCAP that indexes A but not B... the host
         requirements are derived from the BPF for the tcpdump and bpf2tshark
         types and from the native display filter for the tshark type... PCAPs
         lacking a current index entry are always kept... stats are recorded
         under the host_pruning key of the get_pcap_local metadata
       - misc. minor cleanups
       - get_pcap_local now checks that tcpdump/tshark and mergecap can be
         found in the path before generating PCAPs and dies with a clear
         error if not
       - add merge_error key to the get_pcap_local metadata, containing the
         mergecap error message if merging failed
       - filter PCAPs in parallel via Parallel::ForkManager, configurable
         via the new workers config var, settable globally or per set and
         defaulting to 4, with 0 meaning serially in process
       - a empty filter now skips per PCAP filtering and merges the matched
         PCAPs directly, falling back to per PCAP filtering if the direct
         merge fails, such as when one is still being written to
       - skip mergecap when there is only a single PCAP to merge, moving or
         copying it instead
       - try hardlinking before copying when placing the output file
       - cached searches are now listable and fetchable... Virani->list_cached
         and Virani->get_cached, exposed via mojo-virani as the list_cached=1
         and cached=<id> params, with the latter combinable with get_meta=1,
         and remotely fetchable via Virani::Client->list_cached and
         Virani::Client->fetch_cached or virani --list-cached and
         virani --cached <id>
       - the metadata JSON now includes the set it was generated from as the
         key set and the cache ID for fetching it as the key cache_id
       - list_cached and get_cached narrate what they are doing via verbose
         like get_pcap_local does, including warning on unreadable metadata
         JSONs
       - SECURITY: fix default allowed_subnets entry of '192.168.0.0/', which
         parsed as a /0 and matched any IP, to '192.168.0.0/16'
       - bpf2tshark: fix handling of '(', which was never matched, fix ether
         fields being emitted as etc.* instead of eth.*, and don't warn when
         the filter starts with and/or
       - fix cache file naming differing between get_cache_file with and
         without a file specified, causing needless cache misses
       - fix get_cache_file returning undef when auto_no_cache=0 and the
         cache dir is usable
       - fix sets ref check in new checking allowed_subnets instead
       - new_from_conf now reports TOML parse errors properly
       - filter_clean now trims whitespace before the leading '-' check so
         ' -foo' can't slip through
       - bless into the passed class so subclassing works
       - get_pcap_local sets path to undef if the output file was never
         generated and skips the copy
       - dedup option validation between get_cache_file and get_pcap_local
       - cache the Net::Subnet matcher instead of rebuilding it per call
       - remove the unused default_max_time config var
       - require perl 5.10 as named captures are used
       - misc POD fixes, =head1 to =head2 for the check_* methods

1.2.0  2024-10-21/10:#0
       - misc POD cleanup
       - mojo-virani returns 418 now for pcap generation errors

1.1.0  2023-08-12/22:00
       - add ts_is_unixtime and pcap_glob config vars
       - get the set earlier if need for default for get_pcap_local
       - bump depend of File::Find::IncludesTimeRange to 0.2.0
       - misc doc updates

1.0.1  2023-08-07/11:30
       - bpf translate fix for src/dst with out host
       - properly reads type from config
       - log/display padded time
       - display/log BPF translation

0.3.0  2023-08-03/15:45
        - add req_start, req_start_s, req_end, req_end_s, and req_time keys to metadata
        - fix padding handling

0.2.0  2023-08-03/08:45
        - mojo-virani sets content type to application/x-download
        - misc verbosity fixes/cleanup
        - remove needlessly copying the cache file
        - fix typo in name used for syslog messages
        - add etime/stime aliases for start/end args for mojo-virani
        - add --buffer to virani
        - enable special for Time::Piece::Guess
        - misc doc cleanups/updates

0.1.1  2023-07-31/17:30
        - Fix the handling when filter is undef.
        - Minor doc updates.

0.1.0  2023-07-31/12:00
        - Add timestamp logging for when getting a PCAP
        - Support using ARGV for filter info
        - Support reading filter from a file

0.0.1  2023-03-14/13:30
        - Initial release.

